===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{grammar}} A [[word]] that names or refers to a [[person]], [[place]], [[thing]], or [[idea]]. [[noun|Nouns]] and [[personal pronoun]]s are always substantives by nature. Other [[pronoun]]s, [[numeral]]s and most [[determiner]]s readily function as substantives in English and many other languages. When [[present participle]]s function as substantives in English, they are called [[gerund]]s; many other languages prefer to use [[infinitive]]s more often for this purpose. Care in translation is needed when [[adjective]]s are used as substantives, because languages differ in which ones are permitted and which ones must remain adjectives.

An example is that English readily uses an adjective of nationality to mean a language whereas French often requires the noun ''langue'' (language). Further, languages with plural or gendered [[article]]s use these with the substantive adjectives to impart different meanings.

